1
00:00:01,802 --> 00:00:03,937
Joseph: Jotaro, do you hear
what you’re saying right now?

2
00:00:03,971 --> 00:00:04,972
( D’arby growls )

3
00:00:06,273 --> 00:00:08,408
Jotaro: Of course I do.

4
00:00:08,442 --> 00:00:11,779
finally starting
to lose your hearing, old man?

5
00:00:11,812 --> 00:00:14,415
Obviously I just told him
my next pitch.

6
00:00:14,448 --> 00:00:17,818
i’m gonna win
with a high, outside fastball.

7
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:20,854
( Joseph gasps )
But, jotaro, you--

8
00:00:20,888 --> 00:00:22,656
jotaro: Will you believe me,

9
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:25,292
or will you doubt me instead?

10
00:00:25,325 --> 00:00:26,726
( D’arby scoffs )

11
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,596
Not too bright, are you?

12
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:31,966
♪

13
00:00:35,602 --> 00:00:38,405
My stand peers into your soul

14
00:00:38,438 --> 00:00:41,775
the same way a thermal imager
detects an object’s radiation.

15
00:00:41,808 --> 00:00:44,911
Say what you will,
your soul cannot lie.

16
00:00:44,945 --> 00:00:47,948
Regardless of what it is,
by analyzing your soul,

17
00:00:47,981 --> 00:00:51,017
I can see the answer
to any yes-or-no question.

18
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:53,520
Right or left? High or low?

19
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:56,757
Outside or inside?
Fastball or curveball?

20
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:59,726
My stand’s perception
is infallible.

21
00:01:00,961 --> 00:01:02,963
♪

22
00:01:04,998 --> 00:01:07,000
( Singing in Japanese )

23
00:01:25,953 --> 00:01:29,457
Will your pitch be
a high, outside fastball?

24
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:31,725
Yes or no?

25
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:34,694
Jotaro: Yes! Yes!
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

26
00:01:34,728 --> 00:01:38,031
D’arby: Well, jotaro’s
telling the truth, after all.

27
00:01:38,065 --> 00:01:41,435
He’s really going to pitch
a high, outside fastball.

28
00:01:41,468 --> 00:01:43,003
What’s he up to?

29
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:45,438
it’s true that he
beat my brother by bluffing,

30
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:47,240
but he’s a fool if he thinks

31
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:49,910
the same, tired tactic
will work with me.

32
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,012
- Jotaro: Here it comes.
- ( Joseph gasps )

33
00:01:55,816 --> 00:01:58,118
D’arby: For your sake,
I hope you haven’t forgotten

34
00:01:58,151 --> 00:02:01,021
that you’ll lose the game
if you fall 11 runs behind.

35
00:02:01,054 --> 00:02:03,890
♪

36
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:07,328
Was that a curve?

37
00:02:07,361 --> 00:02:08,929
Impossible.

38
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:11,198
I thought he was going
for a high, outside fastball.

39
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:13,133
- Joseph: Eh?
- ( Bat strikes ball )

40
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:15,403
Announcer: He hits,
but it’s a grounder.

41
00:02:15,435 --> 00:02:18,838
The ball is thrown to first,
and out.

42
00:02:18,872 --> 00:02:20,807
( D’arby gasps )

43
00:02:20,841 --> 00:02:22,843
♪

44
00:02:25,779 --> 00:02:28,682
T-there’s just no way.
Everything about him

45
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:31,952
said he was going to throw
a high, outside fastball.

46
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:35,856
his soul can’t lie.
No one’s can, not a zen master,

47
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:39,226
not even my brother, and he’s
the world’s greatest con man.

48
00:02:39,259 --> 00:02:42,229
jotaro: Next up is
another high, outside fastball.

49
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:43,263
( D’arby gasps )

50
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:45,833
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

51
00:02:45,866 --> 00:02:47,801
( D’arby gasps )
What the hell?

52
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:49,303
He’s telling the truth.

53
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:52,873
Jotaro, you have the gall
to cheat your way to victory?

54
00:02:52,906 --> 00:02:55,842
Jotaro: I do! I do!
I do! I do! I do!

55
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:59,046
d’arby: What?
He actually is cheating.

56
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,650
announcer:
A low, inside forkball.

57
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:07,054
it’s a fly ball
heading for the pitcher.

58
00:03:07,087 --> 00:03:08,789
Out.

59
00:03:08,822 --> 00:03:10,991
D’arby: You must have cheated.
Admit it!

60
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,693
You bastard. You clearly
tampered with the console.

61
00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:16,296
Jotaro: No! No! No! No! No! No!

62
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:17,331
D’arby: Wha--

63
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:19,099
he’s telling the truth?

64
00:03:19,132 --> 00:03:21,167
( Panting )

65
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:24,171
( Joseph gasps )

66
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,806
D’arby: I know
you’re cheating me.

67
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:28,675
You have to be. Would you
just come clean already?

68
00:03:31,912 --> 00:03:33,847
No response.

69
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,416
Damn it, that’s right.

70
00:03:35,449 --> 00:03:39,286
I only have use of my power if I
ask him a yes-or-no question.

71
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:41,788
Jotaro: Judging from
your scared expression,

72
00:03:41,822 --> 00:03:44,692
your power requires
a yes-or-no question.

73
00:03:44,725 --> 00:03:46,961
It’s like your brother
used to say.

74
00:03:46,994 --> 00:03:49,363
this is
just a dance of deception

75
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:51,231
where the loser cries first.

76
00:03:51,265 --> 00:03:55,035
D’arby: A dance, eh? So this
is nothing but a game to you?

77
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,938
( Growls ) How dare you?

78
00:03:57,971 --> 00:03:59,873
Are you taking me for a fool?

79
00:03:59,907 --> 00:04:02,309
Have you any idea
who you’re speaking to?

80
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:04,744
Jotaro, pitch the ball!

81
00:04:04,778 --> 00:04:06,747
I’ll figure out
your little trick

82
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:09,116
and take your soul
as my prize!

83
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:13,053
( Jotaro scoffs )
All right, let’s continue.

84
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:17,223
For my next pitch, i’ll throw
a high, outside fastball.

85
00:04:19,393 --> 00:04:22,396
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

86
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:25,799
D’arby: Once again, his soul
says he’s telling the truth.

87
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:28,836
He’s really going to pitch
a high, outside fastball.

88
00:04:28,869 --> 00:04:32,873
I’ve had about as much of this
as I can take. This ends now.

89
00:04:32,906 --> 00:04:34,341
I’ll figure out
how you’re cheating

90
00:04:34,374 --> 00:04:35,976
if it’s the last thing I do.

91
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:38,912
♪

92
00:04:38,946 --> 00:04:41,115
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

93
00:04:41,148 --> 00:04:43,350
D’arby: So jotaro
hasn’t changed his mind.

94
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:47,053
he’s still dead set
on throwing that infernal pitch.

95
00:04:47,087 --> 00:04:48,155
It’s coming.

96
00:04:48,188 --> 00:04:49,723
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

97
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:51,191
D’arby: So far,
it’s still a fastball,

98
00:04:51,225 --> 00:04:52,727
and his soul is saying, "yes."

99
00:04:53,894 --> 00:04:57,431
It changed direction!
a forkball!

100
00:04:57,464 --> 00:05:00,233
what?!
It’s a different pitch now!

101
00:05:00,267 --> 00:05:01,902
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes!

102
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:06,140
umpire: Out.
That’s three outs. Change.

103
00:05:06,173 --> 00:05:08,108
( Joseph sighs )

104
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,876
( D’arby panting )

105
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:11,311
I don’t get it.

106
00:05:11,345 --> 00:05:14,381
Why can’t I figure out
how he’s cheating?

107
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:17,150
Jotaro’s soul kept saying
he’d throw a fastball,

108
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:20,120
but at the last second,
it curved into a forkball.

109
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:23,323
Th-this doesn’t make any sense!

110
00:05:23,357 --> 00:05:26,961
How? How is this wretch
deceiving me?!

111
00:05:29,196 --> 00:05:32,132
Jotaro: You’re gonna
lose this game, d’arby.

112
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:33,668
D’arby: Shut your mouth!

113
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,937
come on. Tell me why
you removed your stupid hat!

114
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,672
I’m more perceptive
than you think.

115
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:41,408
I know you’ve been cheating
ever since you took it off.

116
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:44,878
Now move. I want to check
your station and controller.

117
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:51,151
( Jotaro pats hat )

118
00:05:51,185 --> 00:05:52,219
D’arby: There’s nothing here.

119
00:05:52,252 --> 00:05:55,288
Damn you! How did you do it?!

120
00:05:55,322 --> 00:05:57,958
It must have something to do
with that hat of yours.

121
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:58,992
Isn’t that right?

122
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:00,828
Jotaro: No! No! No! No!

123
00:06:00,861 --> 00:06:01,895
( D’arby gasps )

124
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,699
There must be evidence
around here somewhere.

125
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:08,368
- Jotaro: No! No! No! No!
- D’arby: I get it.

126
00:06:08,402 --> 00:06:10,104
You’re using star platinum
to cheat, aren’t you?

127
00:06:10,137 --> 00:06:12,039
Jotaro: No! No! No! No!

128
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:14,875
D’arby: Just admit it!
You’re doing something!

129
00:06:14,908 --> 00:06:17,344
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes!
yes! Yes! Yes!

130
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,145
( D’arby growls )
damn it.

131
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:21,915
Damn it! I can clearly
read jotaro’s thoughts,

132
00:06:21,949 --> 00:06:25,352
which means my stand’s power
is still working as it should,

133
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:27,621
so how can his mind
say one thing,

134
00:06:27,654 --> 00:06:28,955
but his body do another?

135
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:31,225
Joseph: Hey, jotaro,
are you seeing this?

136
00:06:31,258 --> 00:06:33,660
Looks like he’s losing
his youthful glow.

137
00:06:33,694 --> 00:06:36,797
He definitely doesn’t look like
a guy in his twenties anymore.

138
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:40,000
Jotaro: D’arby, it’s your turn
to pitch, so hurry.

139
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:41,134
We don’t have all day.

140
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:42,302
D’arby: It’s four to three.

141
00:06:42,336 --> 00:06:43,771
with only
a one-point difference,

142
00:06:43,804 --> 00:06:45,372
I might still have a chance.

143
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:48,808
I am a video game genius.
i can’t lose.

144
00:06:48,842 --> 00:06:50,711
I am a video game genius.

145
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:52,079
I can’t lose!

146
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,247
I’ve won every game
i’ve ever played.

147
00:06:54,281 --> 00:06:55,682
I’m invincible.

148
00:06:55,716 --> 00:06:58,085
A video game expert
is an expert at life.

149
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:01,121
do you think you can
shake my confidence so easily?

150
00:07:04,691 --> 00:07:06,660
Announcer: Look at that.
Another home run.

151
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:08,862
That’s another run
for the jaguars, folks.

152
00:07:08,896 --> 00:07:10,664
It’s five to three.

153
00:07:11,698 --> 00:07:14,167
( D’arby groans )

154
00:07:14,201 --> 00:07:15,936
( Doll exhales )

155
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,371
- ( D’arby gasps )
- Joseph: Eh?

156
00:07:19,873 --> 00:07:23,210
( D’arby groans )
I-it can’t be.

157
00:07:23,243 --> 00:07:26,279
I accidentally released
his soul from the doll!

158
00:07:26,313 --> 00:07:28,916
Joseph: Look! His soul
has returned to his body.

159
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:30,384
He’s regaining consciousness.

160
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:32,319
( Kakyoin murmurs )

161
00:07:32,352 --> 00:07:34,020
D’arby: N-no. I didn’t.

162
00:07:34,054 --> 00:07:35,756
I never once admitted defeat.

163
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:37,190
It was an accident.

164
00:07:37,224 --> 00:07:39,927
I didn’t mean to release
his soul from the doll.

165
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:43,030
Jotaro: But the thing is
you did release his soul.

166
00:07:43,063 --> 00:07:44,731
You know what that means.

167
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:47,267
Your soul admitted defeat,

168
00:07:47,301 --> 00:07:49,103
and it’s game over.

169
00:07:50,771 --> 00:07:52,706
D’arby: Huh? Hold on.

170
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:54,374
This is joseph’s stand?

171
00:07:54,408 --> 00:07:57,978
it was wrapped around
the controller the entire time.

172
00:07:58,011 --> 00:08:01,314
Joseph: Huh? Whoops. I guess
I forgot to put this away.

173
00:08:01,348 --> 00:08:03,350
D’arby: How could
something so stupid--

174
00:08:03,383 --> 00:08:05,585
no. You mean it was Joseph?

175
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:07,321
He was the cheater all along?

176
00:08:07,354 --> 00:08:10,257
damn it.
Jotaro was telling the truth.

177
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:12,626
he really
wasn’t controlling it.

178
00:08:12,659 --> 00:08:14,961
It was you, Joseph joestar!

179
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:16,029
Joseph: Hmm?

180
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:19,132
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

181
00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:20,868
Jotaro: That’s right. Good boy.

182
00:08:20,901 --> 00:08:23,103
Too bad you’re not your brother,
’cause if you were,

183
00:08:23,136 --> 00:08:25,338
you would have figured it out
a long time ago.

184
00:08:25,372 --> 00:08:27,941
( D’arby gasping )

185
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,980
Jotaro: By the way, old man,
you’re pretty clever.

186
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:35,315
I didn’t expect you
to catch on to my idea

187
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:36,684
as quickly as you did.

188
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:38,385
joseph: Well,
of course I did, my boy.

189
00:08:38,418 --> 00:08:42,255
I can read you like a book.
You are my grandson, after all.

190
00:08:42,289 --> 00:08:44,391
( Chuckles )
Now up and at ’em, kakyoin.

191
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:46,760
- ( Kakyoin gasps )
- D’arby: Damn.

192
00:08:46,793 --> 00:08:49,029
Joseph was controlling things
from behind.

193
00:08:49,062 --> 00:08:50,430
Joseph: Before I forget...

194
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:54,235
What to do with you,
you button-mashing jerk?

195
00:08:54,268 --> 00:08:55,236
D’arby: Oh, shit!

196
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:57,071
Please, mercy! I beg you!

197
00:08:57,104 --> 00:08:59,640
I’ve already given you back
kakyoin’s soul, haven’t I?

198
00:08:59,673 --> 00:09:01,775
It’s like they say,
"no harm, no foul."

199
00:09:01,808 --> 00:09:04,177
We’re good. Right?
Right? Right?

200
00:09:04,211 --> 00:09:06,613
Jotaro: You wanna know
whether i’ll forgive you?

201
00:09:06,647 --> 00:09:10,050
Why don’t you just do what
you do best and read my mind?

202
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:13,220
No! No! No! No! No!

203
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:14,921
( D’arby whimpers )

204
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:17,724
Jotaro: Answer this. Will I
hit you with my right fist

205
00:09:17,758 --> 00:09:19,293
or decide to deck you
with my left?

206
00:09:19,326 --> 00:09:20,727
I’d love to know.

207
00:09:20,761 --> 00:09:22,363
D’arby: Well,
since you’re asking,

208
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:24,131
you’ll use your right one?

209
00:09:24,164 --> 00:09:27,134
Jotaro: No! No! No! No! No!

210
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:28,969
D’arby: Then your left?

211
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:32,138
Jotaro: No! No! No! No! No!

212
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:34,374
D’arby: You’re not
gonna use both, are you?

213
00:09:34,408 --> 00:09:38,746
Jotaro: Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

214
00:09:38,779 --> 00:09:41,148
D’arby: Are you gonna do
the "ora! Ora!" Thing?!

215
00:09:41,181 --> 00:09:45,852
Joseph: Yes, yes, yes!
oh, my god.

216
00:09:45,886 --> 00:09:47,421
( Star platinum yelling )

217
00:09:49,423 --> 00:09:52,359
Narrator: D’arby younger,
out of commission

218
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,661
- star platinum: Ora!
- ( D’arby screams )

219
00:09:54,695 --> 00:09:55,763
( Joseph and kakyoin gasp )

220
00:09:58,098 --> 00:09:59,166
Joseph: How about that?

221
00:09:59,199 --> 00:10:00,867
We broke through
some sort of wall.

222
00:10:00,901 --> 00:10:02,803
That’s our ticket out of here.

223
00:10:02,836 --> 00:10:04,871
Jotaro. Kakyoin.

224
00:10:04,905 --> 00:10:07,841
Jotaro: Good grief.

225
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,910
♪

226
00:10:15,048 --> 00:10:18,018
Man: Forgive me
for disturbing you,

227
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:20,954
but, your excellence,
as i’m sure you’re aware,

228
00:10:20,988 --> 00:10:25,159
joestar and his comrades
have just infiltrated the manor.

229
00:10:25,192 --> 00:10:27,861
regrettably,
I must also inform you

230
00:10:27,895 --> 00:10:30,297
that d’arby has been defeated.

231
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:33,800
( Clock ticking )

232
00:10:33,834 --> 00:10:37,104
dio: Oh?
But d’arby was a genius.

233
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:40,107
how could one
as gifted as d’arby fail me?

234
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,809
come. I’d like
to hear your thoughts.

235
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:46,246
You may enter, cool ice.

236
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:48,249
♪

237
00:10:56,924 --> 00:10:59,493
Cool ice: As you wish.

238
00:11:04,298 --> 00:11:06,233
Dio: Always remember this.

239
00:11:06,266 --> 00:11:10,070
Whatever the obstacle,
whatever the danger,

240
00:11:10,103 --> 00:11:13,373
the joestars are prepared
to sacrifice their lives

241
00:11:13,407 --> 00:11:15,709
in order to save their family.

242
00:11:15,742 --> 00:11:17,978
Kakyoin and the other two--

243
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,080
( Sighs )
What were their names again?

244
00:11:20,113 --> 00:11:24,250
Ah, yes, I believe
it’s avdol and polnareff.

245
00:11:24,284 --> 00:11:26,653
they’re willing
to surrender their lives

246
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:29,657
for the eradication
of yours truly.

247
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:32,760
They believe fleeing from me
is somehow the same

248
00:11:32,793 --> 00:11:35,095
as running from themselves.

249
00:11:35,128 --> 00:11:37,897
Fools, one and all.

250
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:39,299
Nonetheless,

251
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:43,037
the fools find strength
in this misguided belief.

252
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:47,308
D’arby swore his undying
loyalty, but unfortunately

253
00:11:47,341 --> 00:11:51,345
he was not prepared
to actually die on my behalf,

254
00:11:51,378 --> 00:11:54,448
which is why,
at the edge of glory,

255
00:11:54,481 --> 00:11:56,750
victory slipped
through his fingers.

256
00:11:56,783 --> 00:12:01,655
For the rest of eternity,
d’arby will remain in ignorance.

257
00:12:01,688 --> 00:12:03,290
Ice...

258
00:12:03,323 --> 00:12:06,059
have a look
at the scar on my neck.

259
00:12:07,995 --> 00:12:11,065
Jonathan joestar’s body
is still rejecting me,

260
00:12:11,098 --> 00:12:13,934
but I need the blood
of one more soul

261
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:16,002
before this body
truly becomes mine,

262
00:12:16,036 --> 00:12:18,772
and once that happens,
the wound will heal.

263
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:21,875
Ice, will you offer me

264
00:12:21,909 --> 00:12:24,645
the crimson vigor
coursing through your veins?

265
00:12:24,678 --> 00:12:27,681
Cool ice: Yes. It’d be an honor.

266
00:12:27,714 --> 00:12:29,716
♪

267
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,329
What is mine is yours.

268
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:47,067
♪

269
00:12:55,742 --> 00:12:58,111
( Blood pouring )

270
00:12:58,145 --> 00:12:59,813
( Body falls )

271
00:12:59,847 --> 00:13:02,083
♪

272
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:05,251
Dio: Ah, you beheaded yourself.

273
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:07,654
Most splendid.

274
00:13:07,688 --> 00:13:09,156
But, cool ice,

275
00:13:09,189 --> 00:13:12,626
I cannot accept the blood
of such a loyal servant.

276
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:14,094
My wound shall be healed,

277
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:16,830
but it will be
with the blood of another.

278
00:13:16,864 --> 00:13:19,633
For now, you must live,

279
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:22,836
so awaken, and be reborn.

280
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:24,939
Your steadfast resolve

281
00:13:24,972 --> 00:13:29,243
shall secure your victory
over those who’d oppose me.

282
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:31,845
♪

283
00:13:31,879 --> 00:13:35,850
Cool ice: I shall
not fail you, my lord.

284
00:13:35,883 --> 00:13:38,886
dio: No weapon
can surpass one’s own body.

285
00:13:38,919 --> 00:13:40,721
You are ready, cool ice.

286
00:13:40,754 --> 00:13:44,258
Now go, and attend
to our unwanted guests.

287
00:13:45,259 --> 00:13:48,062
Cool ice: I swear, lord dio,

288
00:13:48,095 --> 00:13:51,432
I will not let you down.

289
00:13:51,465 --> 00:13:56,036
You have my word.
I’ll destroy them all.

290
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:58,071
( Stand growling )

291
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:14,120
Dio: Well, I sincerely hope
that for your sake,

292
00:14:14,154 --> 00:14:16,056
your next victim into the void

293
00:14:16,089 --> 00:14:19,392
will be one of the joestars
and not my boudoir.

294
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:23,563
Avdol: The ten minutes
he gave us are up.

295
00:14:23,597 --> 00:14:27,167
I know that Mr. Joestar ordered
us to set the mansion on fire,

296
00:14:27,201 --> 00:14:29,770
but I say we go.
We have to find them.

297
00:14:29,803 --> 00:14:30,804
Polnareff: Agreed.

298
00:14:32,306 --> 00:14:34,108
Avdol: Polnareff,
before we proceed,

299
00:14:34,141 --> 00:14:36,377
there’s something
I need to tell you.

300
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:39,546
listen well. If you
lose your way, get injured,

301
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:42,450
or can’t go on,
I won’t come to your rescue.

302
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:44,150
Make sure you understand that.

303
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:47,454
Same for you, iggy.

304
00:14:47,487 --> 00:14:49,189
I know that might sound cruel,

305
00:14:49,223 --> 00:14:50,624
but remember
the reason we’re here

306
00:14:50,657 --> 00:14:52,692
is to defeat dio
once and for all.

307
00:14:52,726 --> 00:14:56,263
And of course the same rules
must apply to me as well.

308
00:14:56,296 --> 00:14:58,365
if i’m injured
or separated from you,

309
00:14:58,398 --> 00:15:01,434
you have to promise
you won’t attempt to save me.

310
00:15:01,468 --> 00:15:04,538
Above all else, you must think
of your own safety.

311
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:06,440
we can’t
let ourselves get killed

312
00:15:06,473 --> 00:15:09,543
trying to save one another.
There’s too much at stake.

313
00:15:10,844 --> 00:15:13,814
polnareff: Oui.
That’s how it goes, then.

314
00:15:13,847 --> 00:15:16,516
♪

315
00:15:18,685 --> 00:15:20,320
If we get out of this alive,

316
00:15:20,354 --> 00:15:22,323
you’re treating me
to one hell of a meal.

317
00:15:22,356 --> 00:15:24,525
- Avdol: I’ll treat you both.
- ( Iggy grunts )

318
00:15:24,558 --> 00:15:26,260
Polnareff: All right, let’s go.

319
00:15:28,295 --> 00:15:30,664
Do your thing, silver chariot!

320
00:15:32,499 --> 00:15:33,734
( Metal rings )

321
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,602
( Both grunt )

322
00:15:35,636 --> 00:15:37,872
♪

323
00:15:55,088 --> 00:15:57,390
Polnareff: Hey, avdol,
what do we do now?

324
00:15:57,424 --> 00:15:59,459
this place looks
like it goes on forever.

325
00:15:59,493 --> 00:16:01,095
( Avdol sighs )

326
00:16:01,128 --> 00:16:04,264
I know Mr. Joestar told us
to set the mansion on fire,

327
00:16:04,298 --> 00:16:05,800
but setting
this immense labyrinth ablaze

328
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:09,269
would end up putting us
all in danger, so instead...

329
00:16:09,303 --> 00:16:11,372
Magician’s red.

330
00:16:18,412 --> 00:16:19,680
( Both gasp )

331
00:16:19,713 --> 00:16:22,482
Avdol: These flames
detect life-forms.

332
00:16:22,516 --> 00:16:24,251
They can sense anything alive,

333
00:16:24,284 --> 00:16:26,253
detecting
even cutaneous respiration

334
00:16:26,286 --> 00:16:27,754
and minute movements.

335
00:16:27,788 --> 00:16:30,491
These flames can also sense
a stand’s energy,

336
00:16:30,524 --> 00:16:32,493
so we’ll let them lead the way.

337
00:16:32,526 --> 00:16:35,329
Polnareff: Any particular reason
there are six flames?

338
00:16:35,362 --> 00:16:37,331
Avdol: There’s one
for each direction,

339
00:16:37,364 --> 00:16:39,733
as well as for above and below.

340
00:16:39,766 --> 00:16:42,469
If there is anything hidden
within 15 meters,

341
00:16:42,503 --> 00:16:43,738
regardless of its size,

342
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:45,605
the flame
will detect its presence

343
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:47,341
and alert us immediately.

344
00:16:47,374 --> 00:16:50,811
Mr. Joestar and the others
were pulled below us.

345
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:52,479
Let’s head down.

346
00:16:53,547 --> 00:16:55,082
- ( Flames hissing )
- ( Gasps )

347
00:16:55,115 --> 00:16:56,450
the flames
are picking up on something.

348
00:16:56,483 --> 00:16:58,352
apparently it’s
in front of us to the left.

349
00:16:58,385 --> 00:16:59,386
Polnareff: What is?!

350
00:17:05,325 --> 00:17:07,127
Iggy: The fool!

351
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:09,195
♪

352
00:17:11,131 --> 00:17:12,265
( Both gasp )

353
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,268
( Man shrieks )

354
00:17:15,302 --> 00:17:17,104
- ( Both gasp )
- ( Iggy growls )

355
00:17:18,138 --> 00:17:19,439
Polnareff: What the hell?!

356
00:17:19,473 --> 00:17:21,308
Who’s this guy supposed to be?

357
00:17:21,341 --> 00:17:22,542
( Avdol gasps ) Look.

358
00:17:22,576 --> 00:17:24,111
Do you see what’s happening,
polnareff?

359
00:17:24,144 --> 00:17:26,113
Polnareff: Huh? The maze,

360
00:17:26,146 --> 00:17:28,115
it’s totally disappeared!

361
00:17:28,148 --> 00:17:30,651
Avdol: I’m willing to bet
the power of this man’s stand

362
00:17:30,684 --> 00:17:32,319
created the illusion
of the maze.

363
00:17:32,352 --> 00:17:34,788
it dissipated
as soon as iggy slashed him.

364
00:17:34,821 --> 00:17:36,089
( Iggy scoffs )

365
00:17:36,123 --> 00:17:38,125
Narrator: His name, Billie Jean.

366
00:17:38,158 --> 00:17:40,127
His fate, instant defeat.

367
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,429
Avdol: The mansion
is back to normal now,

368
00:17:42,462 --> 00:17:44,764
so we averted
at least one potential crisis,

369
00:17:44,798 --> 00:17:47,734
and the flames don’t seem
to be sensing any danger.

370
00:17:47,768 --> 00:17:49,203
Hmm?

371
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:54,375
( Sighs )

372
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:58,612
( Gasps )

373
00:18:09,056 --> 00:18:10,624
The flames don’t sense a thing,

374
00:18:10,657 --> 00:18:13,593
and iggy hasn’t picked up
on anything either.

375
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,631
( Gasps )

376
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:23,604
my god,
what is that abomination?

377
00:18:23,637 --> 00:18:28,242
Impossible! Neither my flames
nor iggy could sense it.

378
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:30,644
Where did it come from?!

379
00:18:30,677 --> 00:18:34,214
Polnareff, iggy, you have
to get out of here now!

380
00:18:34,248 --> 00:18:35,649
( Both gasp )

381
00:18:37,084 --> 00:18:40,387
♪

382
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:41,421
( Avdol grunts )

383
00:18:50,497 --> 00:18:52,666
Hey, where are you, avdol?!

384
00:18:52,699 --> 00:18:53,800
The hell?

385
00:18:53,834 --> 00:18:56,236
W-what was that thing?
where did it--

386
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:02,543
no, it can’t be.

387
00:19:02,576 --> 00:19:04,044
Whose arms are--

388
00:19:04,077 --> 00:19:07,213
h-hey, avdol, where did you go?!

389
00:19:07,247 --> 00:19:10,283
Avdol, where are you?!

390
00:19:10,317 --> 00:19:12,719
Avdol!

391
00:19:12,753 --> 00:19:15,489
Come out, avdol!

392
00:19:17,424 --> 00:19:19,126
( Stand growls )

393
00:19:20,694 --> 00:19:23,263
polnareff:
W-what the hell is that thing?

394
00:19:23,297 --> 00:19:25,132
Where did it come from?!

395
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:27,300
Weren’t avdol’s flames

396
00:19:27,334 --> 00:19:29,336
supposed to be
able to sense anything?

397
00:19:29,369 --> 00:19:32,806
Hey, iggy, couldn’t your nose
pick up on this thing?!

398
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:35,509
Answer me!

399
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:38,311
( Groans )
Avdol, where are you?!

400
00:19:38,345 --> 00:19:39,847
Where the hell’d you go?!

401
00:19:42,082 --> 00:19:43,250
Stand: Avdol...

402
00:19:45,786 --> 00:19:47,521
( Growls )

403
00:19:47,554 --> 00:19:50,257
Has been reduced
to nothingness.

404
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:52,659
- ( Polnareff sputters )
- ( Iggy pants )

405
00:19:52,693 --> 00:19:55,396
Stand: Beyond my jaws
lies an endless void,

406
00:19:55,429 --> 00:19:57,398
a dark dimension
which harbors things

407
00:19:57,431 --> 00:19:59,800
even I do not fully comprehend.

408
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:04,104
Your ally is dead, but fret not,
as you will soon join him.

409
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:05,338
You were arrogant enough

410
00:20:05,372 --> 00:20:07,441
to believe
you could defeat lord dio,

411
00:20:07,474 --> 00:20:10,110
therefore you must be punished.

412
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:12,145
( Growling )

413
00:20:14,481 --> 00:20:15,749
( Polnareff gasps )

414
00:20:15,782 --> 00:20:18,118
Cool ice: One by one,

415
00:20:18,151 --> 00:20:20,387
each of you shall fall in line

416
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,455
as I scatter
your atomic fragments

417
00:20:22,489 --> 00:20:24,858
across the deepest recesses
of the void.

418
00:20:24,892 --> 00:20:26,660
( Iggy gasps )

419
00:20:26,693 --> 00:20:27,827
( Polnareff sputters )

420
00:20:27,861 --> 00:20:29,329
No, you’re lying.

421
00:20:30,797 --> 00:20:32,499
It’s impossible.

422
00:20:34,234 --> 00:20:36,703
There’s no way you killed avdol.

423
00:20:36,737 --> 00:20:40,441
How dare you lie to me?!

424
00:20:42,743 --> 00:20:44,745
♪

